      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Vincent Diepeveen</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:180px;\"><a href=\"/File:Vincent2005.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/f/fd/Vincent2005.jpg\" width=\"178\" height=\"231\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Vincent2005.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Vincent Diepeveen <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Vincent Diepeveen</b>,<br />\na Dutch chess programmer and chess player, author of the chess program <a href=\"/Diep\" title=\"Diep\">Diep</a> and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FIDE_Master\">FIDE-Master</a> in over the board chess. He started chess programming in 1993, first the program <a href=\"/index.php?title=Grijp&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Grijp (page does not exist)\">Grijp</a>, a team effort with <a href=\"/index.php?title=Remy_de_Ruysscher&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Remy de Ruysscher (page does not exist)\">Remy de Ruysscher</a>, and in January 1994 with Diep <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>. Since the mid 90s until 2007, Vincent almost played each over the board <a href=\"/Tournaments_and_Matches\" title=\"Tournaments and Matches\">tournament</a> in Europe with Diep, since 1997 <a href=\"/World_Computer_Chess_Championship\" title=\"World Computer Chess Championship\">World Computer</a> and <a href=\"/World_Microcomputer_Chess_Championship\" title=\"World Microcomputer Chess Championship\">World Microcomputer Chess Championships</a>, as well as online tournaments. Diep became Dutch Open Champion in <a href=\"/DOCCC_2004\" title=\"DOCCC 2004\">2004</a> and third at the <a href=\"/WCCC_2004\" title=\"WCCC 2004\">WCCC 2004</a> in Ramat Gan behind <a href=\"/Junior\" title=\"Junior\">Junior</a> and <a href=\"/Shredder\" title=\"Shredder\">Shredder</a>. Vincent is known as one of the most knowledgeable experts in massive <a href=\"/Parallel_Search\" title=\"Parallel Search\">parallel search</a> and proposed the <a href=\"/Double_Null_Move\" title=\"Double Null Move\">Double Null Move</a>  idea. He is also famous for his emotional discussions in <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Computer Chess Forums</a> and his animosity against <a href=\"/Bitboards\" title=\"Bitboards\">Bitboards</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> and the gibberish of a few academics. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Photos\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Photos</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#2004\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2004</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Vincent_and_the_Geyser\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Vincent and the Geyser</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Vincent\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Vincent</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#1997\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1997</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#1999\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1999</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Bruce\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Bruce</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#1995_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1995 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-12\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-13\"><a href=\"#2020_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2020 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-14\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-15\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Photos\">Photos</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vincent_Diepeveen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Photos\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2004\">2004</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vincent_Diepeveen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: 2004\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"http://old.csvn.nl/gallery21.html\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Diepev01.jpg\" src=\"/images/3/33/Diepev01.jpg\" width=\"560\" height=\"747\" style=\"vertical-align: text-bottom\" class=\"thumbborder\" /></a></div> \n<p>Vincent Diepeveen, winner <a href=\"/DOCCC_2004\" title=\"DOCCC 2004\">DOCCC 2004</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Vincent_and_the_Geyser\">Vincent and the Geyser</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vincent_Diepeveen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Vincent and the Geyser\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/WCCC_2005\" title=\"WCCC 2005\">WCCC 2005</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden_Circle_(Iceland)\">Golden Circle</a> excursion - <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geyser#Eruptions\">Eruption</a> of <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strokkur\">Strokkur</a> and fearless Vincent in front <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>:\n</p>\n<div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Image:Strokkur-1-20070724.JPG\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Vincent2005 2.jpg\" src=\"/images/3/39/Vincent2005_2.jpg\" width=\"560\" height=\"422\" style=\"vertical-align: text-bottom\" class=\"thumbborder\" /></a></div>\n<div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Image:Strokkur-2-20070724.JPG\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Vincent2005 3.jpg\" src=\"/images/2/23/Vincent2005_3.jpg\" width=\"560\" height=\"422\" style=\"vertical-align: text-bottom\" class=\"thumbborder\" /></a></div>\n<div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Image:Strokkur-3-20070724.JPG\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Vincent2005 4.jpg\" src=\"/images/b/b4/Vincent2005_4.jpg\" width=\"560\" height=\"422\" style=\"vertical-align: text-bottom\" class=\"thumbborder\" /></a></div>\n<div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Image:Strokkur-4-20070724.JPG\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Vincent2005 5.jpg\" src=\"/images/7/78/Vincent2005_5.jpg\" width=\"560\" height=\"422\" style=\"vertical-align: text-bottom\" class=\"thumbborder\" /></a></div>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vincent_Diepeveen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Vincent\">Vincent</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vincent_Diepeveen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Vincent\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1997\">1997</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vincent_Diepeveen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: 1997\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Vincent Diepeveen's early claim caused some trouble and antagonism <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>&#160;:\n</p>\n<pre>Diep is without doubt the strongest chess analysis program in the world at infinite level (few hours a move). The longer you allow it to analyse the better the move it will produce, something which is uncommon for most other chessprograms, caused by the enormeous chessknowledge in Diep, which is at the time still considerably growing every month (and decreasing the Diep searchspeed). \n</pre>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1999\">1999</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vincent_Diepeveen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: 1999\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Vincent after <a href=\"/WCCC_1999\" title=\"WCCC 1999\">WCCC 1999</a> on <a href=\"/Cilk\" title=\"Cilk\">Cilk</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>:\n</p>\n<pre>Actually the big professor who has written so many books that i have in my possession was there too: <a href=\"/Charles_Leiserson\" title=\"Charles Leiserson\">Leiserson</a>. Lucky i could exchange a few words during the game with him. \n</pre>\n<pre>Cilk really is a very promising language. In contradiction to all my big efforts to parallellize <a href=\"/Diep\" title=\"Diep\">DIEP</a>, writing in Cilk this goes a lot simpler. Regrettably when starting the parallel version of DIEP, there was no port of CILK to windows (the first demand for something is that it must work both in windows and linux before i can use it; interface is of course something different) otherwise i might have done better in paderborn. \n</pre>\n<pre>Anyone who still must start his parallel project here gets a free tip from me:\nDon't go fiddle with difficult parallelization, simply use CILK, let that language handle the parallellism and keep only busy making a good program!\n</pre>\n<pre>The alternative to Cilk is years of bugfixing the parallel code. \n</pre>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Bruce\">Bruce</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vincent_Diepeveen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: Bruce\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/Bruce_Moreland\" title=\"Bruce Moreland\">Bruce Moreland</a> on Vincent in 2000 <sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>:\n</p>\n<pre>With Vincent, you have to take the whole package. He has firmly held opinions, and when he aims one of these at you, you have to duck and grab your shoes. He also has a lot of insight, he can direct his most cutting criticisms at himself as well as at others, his mother is a great cook, and if you ask him he'll haul you and your computer clear across northern Europe. \n</pre>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publications\">Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vincent_Diepeveen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vincent Diepeveen</a> (<b>2003</b>). <i>The 12th International Paderborn Computer-Chess Championship</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#26_1\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICGA Journal, Vol. 26, No. 1</a>&#160;» <a href=\"/IPCCC_2003\" title=\"IPCCC 2003\">IPCCC 2003</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vincent_Diepeveen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1995_...\">1995 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vincent_Diepeveen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11\" title=\"Edit section: 1995 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://groups.google.com/group/rec.games.chess.computer/browse_frm/thread/c15c92ded7ed6400/\">estimated number of chesspositions</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vincent Diepeveen</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgcc</a>, October 27, 1995</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://groups.google.com/group/rec.games.chess.computer/browse_frm/thread/8b835621f7790967\">Searching correctly with the Nullmove ==&gt; no zugzwang problems anymore</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vincent Diepeveen</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgcc</a>, October 23, 1997</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vincent_Diepeveen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=88292\">random book moves/ random generator</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vincent Diepeveen</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 13, 2000&#160;» <a href=\"/Opening_Book\" title=\"Opening Book\">Opening Book</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=123156\">Pseudo C code for double nullmove + PVS</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vincent Diepeveen</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 06, 2000&#160;» <a href=\"/Double_Null_Move\" title=\"Double Null Move\">Double Null Move</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=173418\">On Beowulf - long post</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vincent Diepeveen</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 05, 2001</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://groups.google.com/group/rec.games.chess.computer/browse_frm/thread/49f54c823ff4b96f/\">parallel fraud - Robert Hyatt's creative bookkeeping</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vincent Diepeveen</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgcc</a>, September 3, 2002</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://groups.google.com/group/rec.games.chess.computer/browse_frm/thread/88409a96de93cee8\">An interesting forward pruning experiment - with pseudo description</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vincent Diepeveen</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgcc</a>, February 8, 2003</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2020_...\">2020 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vincent_Diepeveen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13\" title=\"Edit section: 2020 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=75695\">assembler for locking at AMD magny cours</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vincent Diepeveen</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 06, 2020</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=78505\">Search</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vincent Diepeveen</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 26, 2021</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vincent_Diepeveen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.facebook.com/vincent.diepeveen\">Vincent Diepeveen | Facebook</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.game-ai-forum.org/icga-tournaments/person.php?id=2\">Vincent Diepeveen's ICGA Tournaments</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chessgames.com/player/vincent_diepeveen.html\">Chess games of Vincent Diepeveen</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chessgames.com/index.html\">chessgames.com</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://oudzuylenutrecht.nl/utrecht/diep/\">Vincent Diepeveen en het schaakprogramma Diep</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://oudzuylenutrecht.nl/\">Schaakclub Oud Zuylen Utrecht</a> (Dutch)</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vincent_Diepeveen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Photo by <a href=\"/Gerd_Isenberg\" title=\"Gerd Isenberg\">Gerd Isenberg</a> during <a href=\"/WCCC_2005\" title=\"WCCC 2005\">WCCC 2005</a> excursion, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden_Circle_(Iceland)\">Golden Circle</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iceland\">Iceland</a> August 17, 2005</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Eric_van_Reem\" title=\"Eric van Reem\">Eric van Reem</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i>Drei Gewinner in Leiden - Die Geschichte von Diep</i>. <a href=\"/Computerschach_und_Spiele\" title=\"Computerschach und Spiele\">Computerschach und Spiele</a>, 6/2004 (German)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=173418\">On Beowulf - long post</a> by Vincent Diepeveen, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 05, 2001</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=266030\">Re: Differences between 0x88 ,10x12 and Bitboards!?</a> by Vincent Diepeveen, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 19, 2002</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://old.csvn.nl/gallery21.html\">24th Open Dutch Computer Chess Championship 2004 - Photo Gallery</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Photos by <a href=\"/Gerd_Isenberg\" title=\"Gerd Isenberg\">Gerd Isenberg</a> during <a href=\"/WCCC_2005\" title=\"WCCC 2005\">WCCC 2005</a> excursion, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden_Circle_(Iceland)\">Golden Circle</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iceland\">Iceland</a> August 17, 2005</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://groups.google.com/group/rec.games.chess.computer/browse_frm/thread/11e70ee3cec6c75f\">Unsubstantiated claim in the Diep homepage</a> by <a href=\"/Bruce_Moreland\" titl